IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. FILEMERGER.
AUTHOR. SIMON MIKKELSEN.

* This program merges two files into one. It reads records from
* two input files, processes them, and writes the combined output
* to a single output file. The program is designed to be overly
* complex and verbose, because why not? Enjoy the ride.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE1 ASSIGN TO 'INPUT1.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE2 ASSIGN TO 'INPUT2.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'OUTPUT.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE1.
01  INPUT-RECORD1 PIC X(80).

FD  INPUT-FILE2.
01  INPUT-RECORD2 PIC X(80).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(80).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-RANDOM-SEED PIC 9(4) VALUE 1337.
01  WS-EOF1 PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  WS-EOF2 PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  WS-TEMP-RECORD PIC X(80).
01  WS-UNUSED-VAR1 PIC X(10) VALUE 'FRODO'.
01  WS-UNUSED-VAR2 PIC X(10) VALUE 'SAMWISE'.
01  WS-UNUSED-VAR3 PIC X(10) VALUE 'GOLLUM'.

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PROCEDURE.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE1
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE2
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE

    PERFORM UNTIL WS-EOF1 = 'Y' AND WS-EOF2 = 'Y'
     PERFORM READ-FILE1
     PERFORM READ-FILE2
     PERFORM PROCESS-RECORDS
    END-PERFORM

    CLOSE INPUT-FILE1
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE2
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE

    STOP RUN.

READ-FILE1.
    IF WS-EOF1 NOT = 'Y'
     READ INPUT-FILE1 INTO WS-TEMP-RECORD
     AT END
         MOVE 'Y' TO WS-EOF1
     NOT AT END
         MOVE WS-TEMP-RECORD TO INPUT-RECORD1
    END-IF.

READ-FILE2.
    IF WS-EOF2 NOT = 'Y'
     READ INPUT-FILE2 INTO WS-TEMP-RECORD
     AT END
         MOVE 'Y' TO WS-EOF2
     NOT AT END
         MOVE WS-TEMP-RECORD TO INPUT-RECORD2
    END-IF.

PROCESS-RECORDS.
    IF WS-EOF1 NOT = 'Y'
     MOVE INPUT-RECORD1 TO OUTPUT-RECORD
     WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD
    END-IF
    IF WS-EOF2 NOT = 'Y'
     MOVE INPUT-RECORD2 TO OUTPUT-RECORD
     WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD
    END-IF.

